..TEXT:
Malatesta, father and son, tyrants of Rimini, who
murdered Montagna, a Ghibelline leader.  Verrucchio was their
castle, near the city.  Of this family were the husband and lover
of Francesca.  Dante calls them mastiffs, becaue of their
fierceness, making "wimbles of their teeth" in tearing and
devouring.
