..TEXT:
Dante, ^Convito~ IV. 28, quoting Cicero, says:
"Natural death is as it were a haven and rest to us after long
navigation.  And the noble soul is like a good mariner; for he,
when he draws near the port, lowers his sails, and enters it
softly with feeble steerage."
